  "heading": "\\(asymmetric)::set.theoretic.relation:on{X}",
  "heading_latex": "\\textrm{asymmetric}\\textrm{ }\\htmlData{mlg-ref=5c7365742e7468656f72657469632e72656c6174696f6e3a6f6e}{\\textrm{relation on }X}",
  "body_text": null,
  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\(asymmetric)::set.theoretic.relation:on{X}]\nRefines: R\nwhen:\n. X is \\set\nsatisfies:\n. forAll: a, b is \\set\n  where:\n  . a \"in\" X\n  . b \"in\" X\n  then:\n  . if:\n    . allOf:\n      . \\set.theoretic.ordered.pair:of{a}:and{b} \"in\" R\n      . \\set.theoretic.ordered.pair:of{b}:and{a} \"in\" R\n    then:\n    . a = b\nDocumented:\n. adjective: \"asymmetric\"\n. written: \"\\operatorname{asymmetric}\"\n. description: \"A relation $R$ on $X$ is asymmetric (in the sense of antisymmetric) when $a \\mathbin{R} b$ and $b \\mathbin{R} a$ together imply $a = b$.\"\nId: \"be2a8627-1584-4738-bd75-ce5836e9e8eb\"",
